Server Stub generation
First you need to include the API definition inside maven project an ideal place to have it is under “src/main/resources/api.yaml”.

To generate the server stubs we uses swagger-codegen https://github.com/swagger-api/swagger-codegen. To make life easier there is a maven plugin developed which you can find at https://github.com/swagger-api/swagger-codegen to generate server stub for CXF.

Add the following plugin to the project.
The generated code will be at “src/gen/java” so we need to add this to the build which can be done by maven build helper plugin as below.
<plugin>
  <groupId>org.wso2.maven.plugins</groupId>
  <artifactId>swagger2msf4j-maven-plugin</artifactId>
  <version>1.0-SNAPSHOT</version>
  <configuration>
      <inputSpec>${project.basedir}/src/main/resources/store-api.yaml</inputSpec>
  </configuration>
</plugin>

Then use “mvn swagger2cxf:generate” command to generate the server stub.


<plugin>
  <groupId>org.codehaus.mojo</groupId>
  <artifactId>build-helper-maven-plugin</artifactId>
  <version>1.9.1</version>
  <executions>
      <execution>
          <id>add-source</id>
          <phase>generate-sources</phase>
          <goals>
              <goal>add-source</goal>
          </goals>
          <configuration>
              <sources>
                  <source>src/gen/java</source>
              </sources>
          </configuration>
      </execution>
  </executions>
</plugin>



